docs.lead_paragraph: BOSTON, June 25. -- There are older American authors than Will Wallace Homey, but not many, for, in spite of the juvenile suggestion of his ordinary signature, he is 78 years of age; but it has only just occurred to him to collect some of his stories and poems contributed to magazines and newspapers during the last forty years.

headline.main: BOSTON GOSSIP OF LATEST BOOKS; A New Volume of Mr. Harney's Stories and Poems Forthcoming -- Some New Editions.
